news.title: Watch: Waymo launches paid robotaxi rides on freeways
news.content: Waymo robotaxis will now take passengers on freeways in three major U.S. cities, marking a major milestone for the driverless, ride-hailing company. The Alphabet-owned company said it'll begin offering those types of trips in the San Francisco, Phoenix and the Los Angeles markets. Waymo also announced an expansion to San Jose, California, where its robotaxis can now pick up and drop off at the SJC airport. The company has been testing robotaxi freeway rides with employees for more than a year.

news.title: SoftBank shares slide as Nvidia stake sale highlights AI funding needs
news.content: TOKYO (Reuters) -SoftBank's shares slid as much as 10% on Wednesday after the $5.8 billion sale of its stake in Nvidia highlighted the growing funding demands it faces to bankroll its "all-in" bet on ChatGPT ​creator OpenAI and other investments.  The conglomerate needs to fund a $22.5 billion follow-on investment in OpenAI, is acquiring chipmaker Ampere in ‌a $6.5 billion deal and has agreed to buy the robotics business of Swiss group ABB for $5.4 billion.  Analyst Mary Pollock at CreditSights estimates SoftBank has committed to at least $41 billion ‌in recent spending on investments and purchases.

news.title: Patrick Ryan’s Buckeye Tops Amazon’s Best Books of 2025 List
news.content: SEATTLE, November 12, 2025--Amazon (NASDAQ: AMZN) today unveiled its Best Books of 2025 list. Patrick Ryan’s Buckeye claims the No. 1 spot, chosen by the Amazon Editors for its captivating multigenerational storytelling. The top five also include Virginia Evans’ The Correspondent, Nina Willner’s The Boys in the Light, Ocean Vuong’s The Emperor of Gladness, and Charlotte McConaghy’s Wild Dark Shore.
